**Animation

Step 1: Right click the res folder.
Then Go to res>New>Android resource directory

Step2: Give the directory name as anim and change
the resource type to anim or animatoraccording to your choice

Step 3: now that the animation folder is created go to
anim>New>Animation resource file

Step 4: give the file any name (in this case roundanimation.xml)
and then click ok

Now are roundanimation.xml file is created

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________
Important XML Animation Attributes In Android:

1) android:duration(="int"): The duration in which animation is completed is referred to as duration attribute.
2) android:fillAfter(="Bool"): This attribute defines whether the view should be visible or not at the end of the
    animation.
3) android:interpolator(="@android:anim/linear_interpolator"): This property refers to the rate of change in animation. You can define your own
    interpolators using the time as the constraint.

4) android:startOffset(="int"): It refers to the waiting time before an animation starts.

5)android:repeatMode(="restart"): When user wants the animation to be repeated then this attribute is used

6) android:repeatCount(="infinite"): This attribute defines the number of repetitions on animation.
______________________________________________________________________________________________________
In order to apply this animation to an object , we will just call the
startAnimation() method of the object. Its syntax is −

ImageView image1 = (ImageView)findViewById(R.id.imageView1);

image.startAnimation(animation);
